attributes.name: sys_id
attributes.description: Unique ID generated by system for user

attributes.name: calendar_integration
attributes.description: Determines whether change requests assigned to that user are sent to their Outlook calendar

attributes.name: sys_created_on
attributes.description: Date this user is created in ServiceNow

attributes.name: sys_created_by
attributes.description: Administrator who created the user in ServiceNow

attributes.name: groups
attributes.description: List of groups the user is part of

attributes.name: roles
attributes.description: List of roles the user is part of

attributes.name: active
attributes.description: Determines whether the user account has been staged for use

attributes.name: password_needs_reset
attributes.description: Determines should the user be prompted to change password at next login

attributes.name: home_phone
attributes.description: Home phone number of the user

attributes.name: ldap_server
attributes.description: LDAP server the user has an account. Identifies which LDAP server authenticates the user when there are multiple LDAP servers

attributes.name: last_login
attributes.description: Last login date of the user

attributes.name: last_login_time
attributes.description: Time of the last login time for the user

attributes.name: locked_out
attributes.description: Determines if user account is locked

attributes.name: notification
attributes.description: Determines if the user should be notified for any changes made on his account.

attributes.name: source
attributes.description: Identifies whether LDAP is used to validate a user. If the Source field starts with ldap, then the user is validated via LDAP. If the Source field does not start with ldap, then the password on the user record is used to validate the user upon login

attributes.name: time_format
attributes.description: Time format selected for user to display time fields

attributes.name: sys_updated_on
attributes.description: Last updated time for the user

attributes.name: sys_updated_by
attributes.description: The last update for the user occurred from

attributes.name: sys_mod_count
attributes.description: Number of updates for the user

attributes.name: vip
attributes.description: Determines if the user is treated as VIP

attributes.name: parent
attributes.description: Parent group of this user group

attributes.name: active
attributes.description: Determines whether the user account has been staged for use

attributes.name: cost_center
attributes.description: Cost centre of the user group

attributes.name: default_assignee
attributes.description: Default assignee for the user group

attributes.name: exclude_manager
attributes.description: Determines if the manager should be excluded for the user group

attributes.name: sys_created_on
attributes.description: Date the user group is created in ServiceNow

attributes.name: sys_created_by
attributes.description: Administrator who created the user in ServiceNow

attributes.name: sys_id
attributes.description: Unique ID generated by system for user group

attributes.name: sys_updated_on
attributes.description: Last updated time for the user group

attributes.name: sys_updated_by
attributes.description: The last update for the user group occurred from

attributes.name: sys_mod_count
attributes.description: Number of updates for the user group

attributes.name: roles
attributes.description: Roles the user group is having

attributes.name: sys_replace_on_upgrade
attributes.description: Replace to out of box version during next upgrade

attributes.name: sys_id
attributes.description: Unique ID generated by system for role

attributes.name: sys_policy
attributes.description: Determines how application files are protected when downloaded or installed

attributes.name: elevated_privilege
attributes.description: This role is an elevated privilege

attributes.name: sys_mod_count
attributes.description: Number of updates for the role
